WEBVTT

00:03.000 --> 00:06.540
Meredith: "Battle." "Fight."

00:06.540 --> 00:10.330
"Win." "Lose."

00:10.330 --> 00:12.000
These are the words we use

00:12.000 --> 00:15.580
when someone is diagnosed
with an illness or a disease.

00:15.580 --> 00:20.170
Catherine:
♪ No wind, no rain ♪

00:20.170 --> 00:24.040
♪ Or winter's cold ♪

00:24.040 --> 00:26.960
♪ Can stop me, baby ♪

00:26.960 --> 00:29.580
♪ Oh, baby ♪

00:29.580 --> 00:32.790
♪ If you're my goal ♪

00:32.790 --> 00:36.920
♪ Ah, ah, ah, ah ♪

00:36.920 --> 00:39.120
We use militarized language

00:39.120 --> 00:40.880
that implies
it's a fair fight.

00:40.880 --> 00:43.080
[ Beeping ]

00:43.080 --> 00:46.920
♪♪

00:46.920 --> 00:49.290
All:
God grant me the serenity

00:49.290 --> 00:52.290
to accept the things
I cannot change,

00:52.290 --> 00:55.420
the courage to change
the things I can,

00:55.420 --> 00:57.880
and the wisdom
to know the difference.

00:57.880 --> 00:59.620
But when it comes
to life and death,

00:59.620 --> 01:02.080
what does winning
really look like?

01:02.080 --> 01:03.960
Is a person a loser for dying

01:03.960 --> 01:06.080
when the outcome isn't really
in their control...

01:06.080 --> 01:08.120
[ Buzzer ]
Oh. Damn it.

01:08.120 --> 01:09.750
If any patients
see you like that,

01:09.750 --> 01:11.580
they might go
to another hospital.

01:11.580 --> 01:12.920
Always gets me
in the mood.

01:12.920 --> 01:14.080
Plus, you know, I'm seeing
what daylight feels like

01:14.080 --> 01:15.080
while I still can.

01:15.080 --> 01:16.290
How's Catherine?

01:16.290 --> 01:18.000
She's ready.

01:18.000 --> 01:18.960
And you?
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

01:20.460 --> 01:22.620
Ah.

01:22.620 --> 01:24.960
Funny bone.
Not as easy as it looks.

01:27.080 --> 01:29.420
Okay, then.
I have real patients,

01:29.420 --> 01:31.920
so, you know,
good luck with...all this.

01:31.920 --> 01:34.790
[ Sighs ]
[ Buzzer ]

01:34.790 --> 01:37.080
I'm messing with you.

01:37.080 --> 01:40.000
You're gonna do great.
You and Amelia.

01:40.000 --> 01:41.960
You're ready.
[ Exhales sharply ]

01:41.960 --> 01:43.330
Charley horse.

01:43.330 --> 01:48.960
♪♪

01:48.960 --> 01:50.380
[ Indistinct talking over P.A. ]

01:50.380 --> 01:52.790
There he is.
Thought you might need this.

01:52.790 --> 01:55.000
Oh. No, thanks.
But I'm -- I'm good.

01:55.000 --> 01:57.210
I'm running late
for Catherine's scans.

01:57.210 --> 01:59.120
Okay, well, I have cleared
all my surgeries today

01:59.120 --> 02:00.170
and shored up child care,

02:00.170 --> 02:01.460
so I'm here for you,
whatever you need,

02:01.460 --> 02:03.290
whenever you need it.
Like I said, I'm good.

02:03.290 --> 02:06.210
Okay, Richard,
it's gonna be a very long day.

02:06.210 --> 02:10.040
Look, Meredith,
I have plenty of doctors

02:10.040 --> 02:11.620
and plenty of friends
looking out for me.

02:11.620 --> 02:14.460
You know who doesn't?
Your father.

02:14.460 --> 02:17.620
Molly had to get back to Bahrain
with her kids.

02:17.620 --> 02:19.290
He's all alone.

02:19.290 --> 02:21.290
And I will make time
to see Thatcher this week,

02:21.290 --> 02:23.290
but today is all
about you and Catherine.

02:23.290 --> 02:24.710
Meredith, Thatcher may not
have a week.

02:24.710 --> 02:28.710
Now, I know it's never been easy
between you two,

02:28.710 --> 02:30.670
but the time to change that
is running out.

02:30.670 --> 02:32.330
♪♪

02:32.330 --> 02:34.080
Excuse me.

02:34.080 --> 02:40.080
♪♪

02:46.880 --> 02:48.330
[ Door opens ]

02:48.330 --> 02:50.080
Richard: Oh, I'm sorry
I missed your scan.

02:50.080 --> 02:53.330
Oh, please.
I went in. I came out.

02:53.330 --> 02:54.920
Same as the first
million times.

02:54.920 --> 02:56.670
Well, I could have
been there for you.

02:56.670 --> 02:58.250
You had a good excuse.

02:58.250 --> 03:01.170
There's my girl!

03:01.170 --> 03:04.380
[ Chuckles ]
There's my girl!

03:04.380 --> 03:06.000
Let me get her for you.
Relax.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.080
[ Giggles ]

03:07.080 --> 03:08.420
Do you want to go
to Grandma?

03:08.420 --> 03:10.920
Say, "Hi, Grandma."
"Hi, Grandma."

03:10.920 --> 03:13.210
Hey!
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

03:13.210 --> 03:14.920
Did Koracick re-check
the CT angio?

03:14.920 --> 03:17.210
Yes,
and please stop.

03:17.210 --> 03:19.210
I appreciate both of you
wanting to be a part of this,

03:19.210 --> 03:21.540
but I have
a crackerjack neuro team.

03:21.540 --> 03:24.040
I need you to be my husband
and my son today.

03:24.040 --> 03:27.420
[ Knock on door ]
Koracick: And we need you
to be our patient.

03:27.420 --> 03:29.580
Hmm, Thomas, you're getting
ready to cut open my spine.

03:29.580 --> 03:31.540
I will be
whatever I want.

03:31.540 --> 03:33.290
Oh. Music to my ears.

03:33.290 --> 03:35.790
Now, we will go in
posteriorly

03:35.790 --> 03:36.790
with our stealth system

03:36.790 --> 03:39.290
and our newly pilfered
ORBEYE scope.

03:39.290 --> 03:42.960
The plan is to go in
and remove it en bloc.

03:42.960 --> 03:44.120
And you really think
that posteriorly

03:44.120 --> 03:45.710
is the way to go?

03:45.710 --> 03:47.460
Oh, it is fun to have so many
surgeons in one family.

03:47.460 --> 03:48.790
Remind me, Avery --

03:48.790 --> 03:51.460
when did you become
double board certified in neuro?

03:51.460 --> 03:52.750
That's really how you talk
to your patient's family?

03:52.750 --> 03:53.830
It is, actually.

03:56.580 --> 03:58.580
We need to
go in posteriorly

03:58.580 --> 04:00.580
to avoid the carotid
and the jugular,

04:00.580 --> 04:03.620
and to avoid having to weave
through the brachial plexus.

04:03.620 --> 04:05.580
Koracick: Look, I know how hard
it is to be on the bench,

04:05.580 --> 04:07.420
but we are the A-Team.
And we don't lose.

04:07.420 --> 04:10.170
Just ask Shepherd's tumor.
Oh, wait, you can't.

04:10.170 --> 04:12.250
Because I removed it.
Flawlessly.

04:12.250 --> 04:14.960
Okay,
any last questions?

04:14.960 --> 04:17.330
Um...it looks like
you've got this.

04:17.330 --> 04:19.080
We do.

04:19.080 --> 04:21.790
Mm-hmm.
[ Smooches ]

04:21.790 --> 04:23.170
I'm good.

04:23.170 --> 04:26.420
But, you know, I-I um...

04:26.420 --> 04:30.790
I think I'd like to
just take a little walk

04:30.790 --> 04:32.290
before we get started.

04:32.290 --> 04:34.790
I'd be happy to --
Oh, no, honey.

04:34.790 --> 04:37.620
I want to go alone.

04:37.620 --> 04:39.290
Koracick: Okay, then,
but no guarantees

04:39.290 --> 04:40.620
I won't watch you
walk away.

04:40.620 --> 04:42.000
You always do.

04:42.000 --> 04:43.330
[ Scoffs ]

04:45.330 --> 04:53.620
♪♪

04:53.620 --> 04:55.790
[ Exhales sharply ]

04:55.790 --> 05:01.330
♪♪

05:01.330 --> 05:06.790
♪♪

05:06.790 --> 05:08.960
[ Exhales sharply ]

05:08.960 --> 05:09.960
[ Doorbell rings ]

05:09.960 --> 05:17.540
♪♪

05:17.540 --> 05:19.330
Hi. I'm --

05:19.330 --> 05:20.710
Meredith?

05:20.710 --> 05:22.000
Yeah.

05:22.000 --> 05:23.250
I'm sorry.

05:23.250 --> 05:25.330
You look just like
your picture.

05:25.330 --> 05:27.500
You're the surgeon,
right?

05:27.500 --> 05:29.040
Yeah.

05:31.670 --> 05:33.750
Uh, do you
want to come in?

05:33.750 --> 05:36.250
That's a loaded
question.

05:36.250 --> 05:37.170
[ Laughs ]

05:45.080 --> 05:47.250
I'm not sure
if he's awake.

05:47.250 --> 05:48.880
He sleeps more and more
these days

05:48.880 --> 05:50.040
as you can imagine.

05:50.040 --> 05:52.250
Uh, can I get
you something?

05:52.250 --> 05:54.500
Water? Gin, maybe?

05:54.500 --> 05:56.790
[ Both chuckle ]

05:56.790 --> 05:59.420
All right.

05:59.420 --> 06:02.710
Thatcher?
You have a visitor.

06:02.710 --> 06:11.290
♪♪

06:11.290 --> 06:13.120
Meredith!

06:13.120 --> 06:14.960
♪♪

06:14.960 --> 06:16.460
Hi...

06:16.460 --> 06:18.460
♪♪

06:18.460 --> 06:19.880
Hi.

06:25.290 --> 06:26.880
He's not on any pain meds.
Clean and sober.

06:26.880 --> 06:28.210
His wishes.

06:28.210 --> 06:30.210
So, just the oxygen,
if he needs it.

06:30.210 --> 06:31.210
But you know
how that works.

06:31.210 --> 06:33.210
I do.

06:33.210 --> 06:34.880
Well,
I'll leave you to it.

06:34.880 --> 06:36.290
My cellphone number
is on the fridge.

06:36.290 --> 06:37.920
If you need anything,
give me a call.

06:38.960 --> 06:40.750
[ Door opens ]

06:43.580 --> 06:44.960
[ Door closes ]

06:50.250 --> 06:53.250
I probably
can't stay very long.

06:53.250 --> 06:55.750
I just...

06:58.250 --> 07:01.000
There's so much to say,
I-I...

07:01.000 --> 07:03.120
I don't know what to say.

07:03.120 --> 07:06.920
I didn't come here
to say anything

07:06.920 --> 07:08.920
or to hear you
say anything to me, so...

07:08.920 --> 07:10.580
we can just sit,
if that's okay.

07:10.580 --> 07:12.420
Okay.

07:37.290 --> 07:44.830
♪♪

07:44.830 --> 07:45.830
[ Door opens ]

07:45.830 --> 07:47.670
Jackson: Mom.

07:47.670 --> 07:49.830
I was looking for you.

07:49.830 --> 07:54.120
♪♪

07:54.120 --> 07:55.880
You know I give Amelia
and Koracick a hard time,

07:55.880 --> 07:57.460
but they're the best.

07:57.460 --> 08:00.330
I was thinking about
my first surgery.

08:00.330 --> 08:03.500
The very first time
I held a scalpel in my hand.

08:03.500 --> 08:06.830
It was a simple lipoma,
but I was terrified.

08:06.830 --> 08:08.880
Hmm.

08:08.880 --> 08:11.380
I expected to feel
so powerful, invincible.

08:11.380 --> 08:13.000
But the second
that scrub nurse

08:13.000 --> 08:15.380
put that 10 blade
in my hand,

08:15.380 --> 08:16.670
I went ice cold.

08:16.670 --> 08:19.330
Okay, so then
what did you do?

08:19.330 --> 08:22.330
Diana Ross.
"Ain't No Mountain High Enough."

08:22.330 --> 08:24.500
The first time
I heard that song,

08:24.500 --> 08:27.670
it just filled me with joy
and such calm...

08:27.670 --> 08:29.080
so I just sang it

08:29.080 --> 08:31.500
over and over and over
in my head, in that O.R.,

08:31.500 --> 08:35.380
until that same sense of calm
and joy washed over me.

08:35.380 --> 08:37.210
And it's been
my secret weapon

08:37.210 --> 08:39.000
for everything
that's ever scared me --

08:39.000 --> 08:40.330
my first surgery.

08:40.330 --> 08:42.750
Labor with you,
it was on an endless loop.

08:42.750 --> 08:44.120
[ Both chuckle ]

08:44.120 --> 08:48.250
Every PET scan,
every MRI.

08:48.250 --> 08:50.710
♪♪

08:50.710 --> 08:52.040
I remember you singing that song
in the kitchen

08:52.040 --> 08:53.880
when I was doing
my homework.

08:53.880 --> 08:55.710
You told me
it was old people music.
[ Laughs ]

08:55.710 --> 08:57.250
[ Laughs ]
You wanted Michael Jackson.

08:57.250 --> 08:59.580
I love me some Michael.
Ooh.

08:59.580 --> 09:01.620
I had to pry that
red leather jacket off of you

09:01.620 --> 09:02.790
to get you to go to bed
at night.

09:02.790 --> 09:05.210
Ah, that's true.

09:05.210 --> 09:07.250
Oh.

09:07.250 --> 09:08.880
I guess I used to do
the same thing.

09:08.880 --> 09:11.880
My first surgery,
I sang a song in my head.

09:11.880 --> 09:14.420
I mean, it calmed me, you know?
I know.

09:14.420 --> 09:16.040
I watched you.

09:16.040 --> 09:18.210
My first --
How did you watch?

09:18.210 --> 09:21.040
Child, please.
I am Catherine Fox.

09:21.040 --> 09:22.250
Do you think
there's a world

09:22.250 --> 09:23.670
where I wouldn't
sneak into the gallery

09:23.670 --> 09:25.460
of my baby's
first surgery?

09:25.460 --> 09:27.420
Oh, you were a sight
to see...

09:27.420 --> 09:29.670
Mm.

09:29.670 --> 09:32.750
I bet Harriet does
the same thing someday.

09:32.750 --> 09:36.580
Well, I'll be sneaking up
into the gallery with you, then.

09:36.580 --> 09:39.330
Deal.

09:39.330 --> 09:42.290
That's a deal.

09:42.290 --> 09:45.080
Now, can we please get you
to your room?

09:45.080 --> 09:47.460
Not yet.

09:47.460 --> 09:48.460
Mom...

09:48.460 --> 09:50.580
I left the foundation
in your name,

09:50.580 --> 09:52.420
just in case
anything happens to me.

09:52.420 --> 09:54.420
Cecilia runs
the day-to-day operations,

09:54.420 --> 09:56.250
Charlie keeps
the books humming,

09:56.250 --> 09:59.250
but they'll need a leader,
a North Star.

09:59.250 --> 10:01.000
And in the event that I'm left
totally paralyzed --

10:01.000 --> 10:02.580
Mom, even if
you can't operate,

10:02.580 --> 10:03.580
you're still gonna run
the foundation, okay?

10:03.580 --> 10:05.120
You'll teach.

10:05.120 --> 10:07.120
You're Catherine Fox.
What are you gonna do?

10:07.120 --> 10:08.040
You're gonna be all up
in my business

10:08.040 --> 10:09.620
and everybody else's.

10:09.620 --> 10:10.620
We both know you're gonna
find a way to do that.

10:10.620 --> 10:13.040
Keep this.
Turn the page.

10:13.040 --> 10:15.210
I've already --
Turn the page.

10:15.210 --> 10:17.120
♪♪

10:17.120 --> 10:18.460
You planned
your own party?

10:18.460 --> 10:20.120
[ Laughs ]
Mom.

10:20.120 --> 10:22.670
If I get out of this alive,
the fun we're gonna have --

10:22.670 --> 10:25.040
and don't you even think about
scrimping on those egg rolls.

10:25.040 --> 10:26.670
You know
they're my favorite.

10:26.670 --> 10:30.290
You really
planned everything.

10:30.290 --> 10:33.040
I always do.

10:33.040 --> 10:34.290
All right, then.

10:34.290 --> 10:37.460
Shall we?

10:37.460 --> 10:40.040
[ Exhales deeply ]

10:40.040 --> 10:41.040
[ Smooches ]

10:41.040 --> 10:44.290
♪♪

10:44.290 --> 10:47.330
Thatcher:
Victoria Falls, Zimbabwe.

10:47.330 --> 10:50.250
Phillip put these everywhere
for me.

10:50.250 --> 10:52.380
He said it's supposed to
be soothing.

10:52.380 --> 10:54.000
Truth be told,

10:54.000 --> 10:55.830
it just makes me
miss it more.

10:55.830 --> 10:57.670
[ Chuckles ]

10:57.670 --> 11:00.040
A few years back,
a student told me about

11:00.040 --> 11:03.710
a semester he took abroad
building schools.

11:03.710 --> 11:08.170
Lexie was gone,
and I thought I could either

11:08.170 --> 11:09.500
drown my grief
in a bottle of Scotch

11:09.500 --> 11:11.670
or do something.
So I did something.

11:11.670 --> 11:13.830
[ Chuckles ]

11:15.540 --> 11:17.170
In Zimbabwe.

11:17.170 --> 11:21.750
The sunsets, Meredith...
and the quiet.

11:21.750 --> 11:24.670
The people that I met,
they have this passion

11:24.670 --> 11:28.710
for life, loving,
learning...

11:32.120 --> 11:34.880
And then you got sick.

11:34.880 --> 11:37.250
[ Sighs ] I thought
I'd just come home,

11:37.250 --> 11:38.620
do whatever treatment
I needed to do,

11:38.620 --> 11:41.880
and then go back, but...
It was good. Coming home.

11:41.880 --> 11:46.250
It gave me a chance to --
It was the right thing to do.

11:50.380 --> 11:52.380
You went and got
a whole new life.

11:52.380 --> 11:54.080
I did.
[ Sighs ]

11:55.710 --> 11:57.540
I'm glad for you.

11:57.540 --> 12:00.380
I'm glad you saw sunsets
and built schools

12:00.380 --> 12:02.960
for people who needed them
and you stayed sober.

12:02.960 --> 12:04.580
You went and got
a whole new life.

12:04.580 --> 12:09.040
Halfway across the world
this time.

12:09.040 --> 12:10.290
But you didn't
give a damn

12:10.290 --> 12:11.580
about the people
you left behind.

12:15.580 --> 12:17.620
Say it again.

12:17.620 --> 12:20.170
We make an incision posteriorly
from C3 to T4,

12:20.170 --> 12:21.580
and then use
the stealth probe

12:21.580 --> 12:23.170
to mark the coordinates
of the tumor.

12:23.170 --> 12:25.000
And then do
partial laminectomies

12:25.000 --> 12:27.790
to access the tumor
and remove it en bloc.

12:27.790 --> 12:28.960
Perfect. Brilliant.

12:28.960 --> 12:30.420
We are incredible.

12:30.420 --> 12:31.790
Someone should really do
a study on us.

12:31.790 --> 12:34.170
[ Chuckles,
exhales sharply ]

12:34.170 --> 12:35.790
Okay, say it.

12:35.790 --> 12:38.170
What? Wh--
Oh. No.

12:38.170 --> 12:40.580
Ha ha! I'm good.

12:40.580 --> 12:43.420
Good, good, good, good.
Big Gun.

12:43.420 --> 12:44.920
Ready to Big Gun the crap
out of this tumor.

12:44.920 --> 12:46.080
[ Chuckles nervously ]

12:47.290 --> 12:49.120
Damn it.

12:49.120 --> 12:51.000
Even my arrogance is off.
Right?

12:51.000 --> 12:53.290
Right.

12:53.290 --> 12:55.290
W-What if we try, uh,
your thing?

12:55.290 --> 12:57.460
You know, the -- the word-vomit
and the feelings?

12:57.460 --> 12:59.540
That seems to work.
For you.

12:59.540 --> 13:01.040
Okay.

13:01.040 --> 13:02.620
You -- you first.

13:04.500 --> 13:06.710
This is the largest tumor
I've ever seen

13:06.710 --> 13:08.120
on the biggest legend
I've ever known,

13:08.120 --> 13:10.120
and if I screw this up,
I'm gonna have to live out

13:10.120 --> 13:11.120
the rest of my
ill-fated surgical career

13:11.120 --> 13:12.290
fixing idiot teenagers

13:12.290 --> 13:13.500
who get hurt cow-tipping
in Lawrence, Kansas,

13:13.500 --> 13:14.710
'cause I can't look
Richard in the eye

13:14.710 --> 13:16.170
knowing I gorked
his legend wife.

13:16.170 --> 13:18.210
That is specific.

13:18.210 --> 13:20.000
Well...
I'm saying,

13:20.000 --> 13:22.170
how do you get hurt
cow-tipping?
It's a thing.

13:22.170 --> 13:24.880
Just...You. Go.

13:24.880 --> 13:27.290
Uh, Catherine Fox is an icon,
and a magician,

13:27.290 --> 13:28.880
and a giant among men --

13:28.880 --> 13:30.880
and not just
for the reasons you think.

13:30.880 --> 13:32.460
She's saved more penises
in her O.R.

13:32.460 --> 13:33.920
than any surgeon
on the planet.

13:33.920 --> 13:35.330
And all I keep imagining

13:35.330 --> 13:36.670
are the dozens of men
with zero-functioning penises,

13:36.670 --> 13:38.040
doomed to live out
their sexless lives

13:38.040 --> 13:39.920
if I botch this surgery.

13:39.920 --> 13:42.330
That's what
you're worried about?

13:42.330 --> 13:43.710
Men and their junk?

13:43.710 --> 13:46.080
That,
and if I lose her...

13:48.080 --> 13:49.920
I've lost enough.

13:51.380 --> 13:52.750
So let's keep her alive.

13:52.750 --> 13:55.380
♪♪

13:55.380 --> 13:56.540
Let's keep her alive.

13:56.540 --> 14:03.170
♪♪

14:03.170 --> 14:05.500
[ Inhales sharply ]

14:05.500 --> 14:10.920
♪♪

14:10.920 --> 14:12.880
I told them I didn't need
a personal escort

14:12.880 --> 14:14.920
to my own surgery.

14:14.920 --> 14:16.290
Well,
that's just making sure

14:16.290 --> 14:18.120
you don't make a break
for it.

14:18.120 --> 14:20.120
Thomas,
make sure that I wake up

14:20.120 --> 14:23.120
with good motor
and nerve function.

14:23.120 --> 14:26.080
And don't forget
to get clean margins.

14:26.080 --> 14:27.080
I wouldn't dream of it.

14:27.080 --> 14:28.540
And would
you tell my husband

14:28.540 --> 14:30.710
he does not have to sit up
in that gallery all day?

14:30.710 --> 14:31.880
"For better, for worse"

14:31.880 --> 14:34.080
does not include
seeing your wife's insides.

14:34.080 --> 14:35.710
You know,
you wouldn't be you

14:35.710 --> 14:37.540
if you weren't
bossing us all around

14:37.540 --> 14:39.120
up until
the last second.

14:39.120 --> 14:42.210
Amelia: You nervous?

14:42.210 --> 14:43.540
[ Exhales sharply ]
Were you?

14:43.540 --> 14:47.040
A little bit.
But I turned out just fine.

14:47.040 --> 14:48.120
That's because
I was perfect,

14:48.120 --> 14:50.460
which I'm willing
to be again.

14:50.460 --> 14:51.580
Richard:
Well, you better be.

14:51.580 --> 14:52.750
Oh, Richard,
I always liked you.

14:52.750 --> 14:54.290
No, you didn't.

14:54.290 --> 14:56.080
And I'm fine
as long as she's fine.

14:56.080 --> 14:58.330
Okay, okay, can I have a minute
with my husband, please?

15:17.250 --> 15:20.750
I will see you...
when I wake up.

15:20.750 --> 15:22.620
Jackson?

15:22.620 --> 15:25.080
Where's Jackson?

15:25.080 --> 15:26.960
[ Diana Ross' "Ain't No Mountain
High Enough" plays ]

15:26.960 --> 15:27.750
[ Laughs ]
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

15:27.750 --> 15:28.920
One for the road?

15:28.920 --> 15:32.170
Oh, ha ha!
My baby!

15:32.170 --> 15:35.290
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪
[ Sighs ]

15:36.790 --> 15:39.790
[ Screams, laughs ]

15:39.790 --> 15:45.960
[ Vocalizing ]

15:45.960 --> 15:49.540
♪ If you need me ♪

15:49.540 --> 15:52.120
♪ Call me ♪

15:52.120 --> 15:54.460
♪ No matter where you are ♪

15:54.460 --> 15:56.670
♪ No matter how far ♪

15:56.670 --> 15:58.880
♪ No wind ♪
♪ No wind ♪

15:58.880 --> 16:00.460
♪ No rain ♪
♪ No rain ♪

16:00.460 --> 16:03.040
♪ Can stop me, babe ♪

16:03.040 --> 16:06.120
♪ If you're my goal ♪

16:06.120 --> 16:11.380
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

16:11.380 --> 16:14.040
♪ Ain't no mountain
high enough ♪
♪ Oh, oh-oh ♪

16:14.040 --> 16:16.790
♪ Ain't no valley low enough ♪
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

16:16.790 --> 16:18.540
♪ Ain't no river
wide enough ♪
♪ Oh, oh ♪

16:18.540 --> 16:21.540
♪ To keep me from you ♪

16:21.540 --> 16:26.580
♪ Ain't no mountain
high enough ♪

16:26.580 --> 16:31.330
♪ Nothing can keep me,
keep me from you ♪

16:31.330 --> 16:33.250
♪ Ain't no mountain high enough
to keep me from you ♪

16:40.500 --> 16:41.670
[ The Commitments'
"Mustang Sally" plays ]

16:41.670 --> 16:45.040
♪ You've been running
all over town ♪

16:45.040 --> 16:48.250
Koracick: Just like that,
we are ready to navigate.

16:48.250 --> 16:51.500
Amelia: Don't you want to
confirm the accuracy first?

16:51.500 --> 16:52.670
Oh, what would I do
without someone here

16:52.670 --> 16:54.670
to remind me
of the obvious?

16:54.670 --> 16:57.040
I'm just saying,
maybe a little less music,

16:57.040 --> 16:58.500
a little more
concentration.

16:58.500 --> 17:02.710
♪ All you want to do
is ride around, Sally ♪

17:02.710 --> 17:05.080
♪ Ride, Sally, ride ♪

17:05.080 --> 17:06.790
Whoo!

17:06.790 --> 17:09.420
This is going to be
a long day.

17:09.420 --> 17:13.580
And you are gonna love
every minute of it.

17:13.580 --> 17:15.210
We're gonna get down
in there.

17:15.210 --> 17:17.040
Get down and dirty.
Here we go.

17:17.040 --> 17:19.580
♪ All you want to do
is ride around, Sally ♪

17:19.580 --> 17:23.960
♪ Ride, Sally, ride ♪

17:23.960 --> 17:27.880
♪ All you want to do
is ride around, Sally ♪

17:27.880 --> 17:29.120
Mind if I join you?

17:29.120 --> 17:30.710
♪ Ride, Sally, ride ♪

17:30.710 --> 17:32.080
I'd like that.

17:32.080 --> 17:35.790
♪ One of these early mornings ♪

17:35.790 --> 17:36.920
♪ I'm gonna be wiping
those weeping eyes ♪

17:36.920 --> 17:39.290
How's the resection
going?

17:39.290 --> 17:41.210
So far so good.

17:41.210 --> 17:43.460
Koracick: Come on.
Let it loose. Let it out.

17:43.460 --> 17:45.460
Are you sure you don't want
to be in the waiting room?

17:45.460 --> 17:47.330
I can watch, and I can report
back to you guys.

17:47.330 --> 17:49.920
No, I'm fine right where I am.
I-I'm good.

17:49.920 --> 17:51.250
♪ I bought you
a brand-new mustang ♪

17:53.420 --> 17:55.000
Do it with me.
Come on, now.

17:55.000 --> 17:57.000
You're mad.

17:57.000 --> 17:58.250
Meredith:
I'm not mad.

17:58.250 --> 18:00.670
Meredith...

18:00.670 --> 18:02.500
Fine. I'm mad.

18:02.500 --> 18:04.080
Because I moved away.

18:04.080 --> 18:06.330
Because you ran away.

18:06.330 --> 18:09.460
Because you have never fought
for anyone or anything

18:09.460 --> 18:11.670
that you cared for
in your life.

18:11.670 --> 18:13.670
You just disappear.

18:13.670 --> 18:16.250
When I gave you
a piece of my liver,

18:16.250 --> 18:18.250
you said we would try,
right?

18:18.250 --> 18:20.420
You said we could
get to know each other.

18:20.420 --> 18:23.080
You didn't try.
You didn't fight.

18:23.080 --> 18:24.580
And when Lexie died --

18:24.580 --> 18:25.960
I know. I know.
No, you don't know,

18:25.960 --> 18:27.380
because you weren't here.

18:27.380 --> 18:30.620
I lost my sister.
I lost my husband.

18:30.620 --> 18:32.170
And you were
nowhere to be found.

18:32.170 --> 18:33.380
That's not --
[ Clears throat ]

18:33.380 --> 18:36.880
Meredith, I was there
after Derek died.

18:36.880 --> 18:38.290
No, why would you say
something like that?

18:38.290 --> 18:40.290
Because it's the truth,
Meredith.

18:40.290 --> 18:42.040
Richard told me Derek died.
I bought a ticket.

18:42.040 --> 18:43.290
I flew all day,
all night.

18:43.290 --> 18:46.040
I got to the funeral just --
just in time.

18:46.040 --> 18:48.120
I stood a few rows back.
[ Scoffs ]

18:48.120 --> 18:50.880
Next to some of your doctor
friends from the hospital.

18:50.880 --> 18:53.670
I would remember
if you were at his funeral.

18:53.670 --> 18:54.960
I was there, Meredith.

18:54.960 --> 18:57.460
But you were barely there.
You were a ghost.

18:57.460 --> 19:00.670
You looked like me
when I lost Susan and Lexie.

19:00.670 --> 19:02.330
Are you saying
you came to the funeral

19:02.330 --> 19:03.790
and didn't speak to me?

19:03.790 --> 19:06.460
I felt like it would --
would have been for me,

19:06.460 --> 19:09.000
not -- [ Coughs ]
not -- not -- [ Coughs ]

19:09.000 --> 19:12.000
for -- [ Coughs ]
for you.

19:12.000 --> 19:13.080
[ Coughing, wheezing ]

19:13.080 --> 19:15.500
Let's get you
to the bed.

19:15.500 --> 19:17.170
[ Coughing ]

19:17.170 --> 19:23.500
♪♪

19:23.500 --> 19:29.920
♪♪

19:29.920 --> 19:33.000
[ Coughing, wheezing ]

19:33.000 --> 19:35.170
♪♪

19:35.170 --> 19:37.380
[ Oxygen hisses ]

19:37.380 --> 19:41.170
I came home, Meredith.
For you.

19:41.170 --> 19:47.830
♪♪

19:47.830 --> 19:49.620
[ The Talking Heads' "This
Must Be the Place" plays ]

19:49.620 --> 19:53.210
♪ And you're standing
here beside me ♪

19:53.210 --> 19:55.420
This microscope
is a game changer.

19:55.420 --> 19:56.540
I know. I feel like I could
just walk into the screen

19:56.540 --> 19:59.380
and surf
on the spinal cord.

19:59.380 --> 20:02.290
♪ Never for money,
always for love ♪

20:02.290 --> 20:05.880
♪ Cover up
and say goodnight ♪

20:05.880 --> 20:07.460
♪ Say goodnight ♪

20:07.460 --> 20:09.290
All right...

20:09.290 --> 20:13.380
it looks like we are clear
to remove the tumor en bloc.

20:13.380 --> 20:14.960
[ Music continues ]

20:14.960 --> 20:16.460
Except -- hang on.

20:16.460 --> 20:18.710
♪♪

20:18.710 --> 20:20.210
I can't get it free.

20:20.210 --> 20:21.790
Okay, then.
Time to suck and pluck.

20:21.790 --> 20:23.210
I'm sorry, what?
The tumor's like a grape.

20:23.210 --> 20:24.710
You suck out the inside,
then you pluck out the skin.

20:24.710 --> 20:26.380
Suck and pluck.

20:26.380 --> 20:27.880
Could you call it
something else?
Like what?

20:27.880 --> 20:30.620
Literally anything else.

20:30.620 --> 20:32.250
[ Humming ]

20:32.250 --> 20:34.420
Jackson: [ Scoffs ]
I hate this dude.

20:34.420 --> 20:36.420
-Jackson, sit.
-No, I hate him. For real.

20:36.420 --> 20:37.580
I want to jump
through this glass

20:37.580 --> 20:38.960
and just, like,
choke him out.

20:38.960 --> 20:39.960
He is bopping.

20:39.960 --> 20:42.080
He's bopping
over my mom's spine.

20:42.080 --> 20:43.920
I mean, who does that?
Maybe you should take a walk.

20:43.920 --> 20:45.830
I'm gonna
take a walk now.

20:45.830 --> 20:49.420
[ Humming ]

20:49.420 --> 20:53.080
Richard, this can't be good
for you either.

20:54.920 --> 20:57.920
The first year or so
Catherine and I were together,

20:57.920 --> 21:00.080
we figured out how to make
the long distance work

21:00.080 --> 21:02.330
because we'd promise
to show up

21:02.330 --> 21:04.830
whenever we needed,
however we needed.

21:04.830 --> 21:06.790
It's what you do
for the people you love.

21:06.790 --> 21:09.790
She may fuss,

21:09.790 --> 21:13.620
but I don't need to ask her
where she wants me to be.

21:13.620 --> 21:15.460
I'm already here.

21:15.460 --> 21:17.460
♪ Make it up as we go along ♪

21:17.460 --> 21:19.210
Are you okay if I --

21:19.210 --> 21:20.960
It's fine. Go.

21:20.960 --> 21:22.790
♪ Head in the sky ♪

21:22.790 --> 21:26.210
♪ It's okay,
I know nothing's wrong ♪

21:26.210 --> 21:29.620
♪ Nothing's wrong, oh ♪

21:29.620 --> 21:31.620
♪ I got plenty of time ♪

21:31.620 --> 21:34.540
You gonna lecture me, too,
on how I shouldn't be here?

21:34.540 --> 21:35.960
You shouldn't be.

21:35.960 --> 21:37.830
♪ Oh, you got light
in your eyes ♪

21:37.830 --> 21:40.210
But that's not my call.

21:40.210 --> 21:43.170
It's not decompressing.
What do you mean
it's not decompressing?

21:43.170 --> 21:44.540
It's too dense,
like it's made of --

21:44.540 --> 21:46.120
I don't know what --
cartilage,

21:46.120 --> 21:49.290
small chips
of hard calcifications.

21:49.290 --> 21:50.790
Damn it.
I can't get it either.

21:50.790 --> 21:52.040
Kill the music.

21:52.040 --> 21:54.170
[ Music stops ]

21:56.170 --> 21:58.170
We need to go in
from the front.

21:58.170 --> 22:00.670
Her spine is open.

22:00.670 --> 22:01.880
It's all exposed.

22:01.880 --> 22:03.330
If we move her,

22:03.330 --> 22:05.420
we risk losing function
in her forearm and hand.

22:05.420 --> 22:06.580
It's the only way.

22:06.580 --> 22:10.000
Okay, well, let me ask you
one question first --

22:10.000 --> 22:11.880
Are you insane?
We close up the incision.

22:11.880 --> 22:13.330
We flip her onto her side.
I go in from the front.

22:13.330 --> 22:14.500
We meet in the middle
to decompress

22:14.500 --> 22:15.500
and unearth this thing.

22:15.500 --> 22:17.040
So the answer is yes,
you are insane.

22:17.040 --> 22:18.540
We'll get a few more people
in here, we can flip her.

22:18.540 --> 22:20.380
And keep her still
and not sever her spine?

22:20.380 --> 22:22.170
Not to mention having
to break scrub,

22:22.170 --> 22:24.000
re-drape, rescrub --
Cow-tipping in Kansas!

22:24.000 --> 22:25.170
Dozens of sexless men!

22:25.170 --> 22:27.000
If it were you again
on the table,

22:27.000 --> 22:28.670
what would you want?

22:28.670 --> 22:33.210
♪♪

22:33.210 --> 22:34.500
[ Exhales sharply ]

22:34.500 --> 22:37.120
♪♪

22:37.120 --> 22:38.620
For the record,
I do not like you.

22:38.620 --> 22:42.790
♪♪

22:42.790 --> 22:44.210
Shut down the gallery.

22:44.210 --> 22:47.250
♪♪

22:54.540 --> 22:57.540
[ Indistinct talking over P.A. ]

22:57.540 --> 22:59.210
There you are.

23:02.710 --> 23:04.710
[ Exhales sharply ]

23:08.620 --> 23:12.420
Mom's always been
larger than life, you know?

23:12.420 --> 23:16.040
Laughs harder,
yells louder than anyone.

23:16.040 --> 23:18.000
She's the life
of the party.

23:18.000 --> 23:19.420
Even if it's
my birthday party

23:19.420 --> 23:21.000
and she's taking over
the dance floor.

23:21.000 --> 23:22.830
[ Laughs ]
[ Sighs ]

23:22.830 --> 23:24.250
Sounds amazing.

23:24.250 --> 23:25.620
I was 16.
It was mortifying.

23:25.620 --> 23:27.420
[ Laughs ]

23:27.420 --> 23:30.580
[ Sighs ]
She'd always do that.

23:30.580 --> 23:32.000
She always
inserted herself

23:32.000 --> 23:34.420
in every single aspect
of my life, you know,

23:34.420 --> 23:35.790
whether I wanted her to
or not --

23:35.790 --> 23:39.080
Hell, whether I even knew
about it or not.

23:39.080 --> 23:40.500
[ Exhales sharply ]

23:40.500 --> 23:42.080
And, um...

23:45.790 --> 23:49.620
Now I can't, uh...

23:49.620 --> 23:54.080
I can't imagine what a room
would even feel like

23:54.080 --> 23:59.460
without her in it
taking up all that space.

23:59.460 --> 24:05.290
It was different...
losing Samuel.

24:10.120 --> 24:13.880
[ Voice breaking ]
That was more like --

24:13.880 --> 24:15.830
like my world collapsing
around me, you know?

24:15.830 --> 24:17.670
And this, I just...

24:20.540 --> 24:24.790
I feel like...
a scared little kid.

24:28.380 --> 24:33.170
[ Voice breaking ]
Like nothing is safe.

24:33.170 --> 24:34.620
Like the world's
upside down

24:34.620 --> 24:36.380
and nothing makes any sense
anymore.

24:36.380 --> 24:38.830
Yeah.
Yeah.

24:38.830 --> 24:41.420
[ Crying ] I don't like it.
I know.

24:41.420 --> 24:45.580
I don't like it.
[ Crying ] I know. I know.

24:45.580 --> 24:48.580
[ The Rescues' "Hold On" plays ]

24:48.580 --> 24:51.380
♪ Hold on ♪

24:51.380 --> 24:55.380
♪ Hold on to yourself ♪

24:55.380 --> 25:01.250
♪ For this is gonna
hurt like hell ♪

25:01.250 --> 25:04.500
♪♪

25:04.500 --> 25:07.250
Koracick: Okay.
Let's rock and roll.

25:07.250 --> 25:11.540
On my count,
one, two, three.

25:11.540 --> 25:14.710
♪♪

25:14.710 --> 25:17.250
Good, good, good.
Easy.

25:17.250 --> 25:19.830
♪♪

25:19.830 --> 25:23.790
♪ So now you're sleeping
peaceful ♪

25:23.790 --> 25:27.540
♪ I lie awake and pray ♪

25:27.540 --> 25:29.710
♪ That you'll be strong
tomorrow ♪

25:29.710 --> 25:31.250
Let's secure her hips.

25:31.250 --> 25:34.250
♪ And will see another day ♪

25:34.250 --> 25:37.880
♪ And we will praise it ♪

25:37.880 --> 25:39.540
She's good.

25:39.540 --> 25:42.380
♪ And love the light
that brings a smile ♪

25:42.380 --> 25:45.210
Okay, they did it.
She's okay.

25:45.210 --> 25:46.290
♪ Across your face ♪

25:46.290 --> 25:51.880
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, hold on ♪

25:51.880 --> 25:54.540
♪ Oh, God ♪

25:54.540 --> 25:58.710
♪ If you're out there,
won't you hear me? ♪

25:58.710 --> 26:02.380
♪ I know that we have never
talked before ♪

26:02.380 --> 26:04.420
♪ I know that we have never ♪

26:04.420 --> 26:05.580
You ready, Bokie?

26:05.580 --> 26:07.580
♪ Talked before ♪

26:07.580 --> 26:08.920
♪ Oh, God ♪

26:08.920 --> 26:10.580
Amelia: Okay.
Deep breath, everybody.

26:10.580 --> 26:11.750
♪ The one I love ♪
Scalpel.

26:11.750 --> 26:13.960
♪ Is leaving ♪

26:13.960 --> 26:21.960
♪ Don't you take her
when she comes to your door ♪

26:21.960 --> 26:26.000
♪♪

26:26.000 --> 26:27.670
Amelia: Dr. Koracick?

26:27.670 --> 26:30.460
♪♪

26:30.460 --> 26:31.330
Tom.

26:33.250 --> 26:34.620
I think
I'm gonna have trouble

26:34.620 --> 26:37.080
getting around
the C7 facet

26:37.080 --> 26:40.000
while keeping the tumor
retracted from this angle.

26:40.000 --> 26:41.330
Maybe you could give it
a try?

26:41.330 --> 26:44.830
♪ And love the light
that brings a smile ♪

26:44.830 --> 26:47.790
Please,
I could do that in my sleep.

26:47.790 --> 26:48.790
♪ Across your face ♪
Show off.

26:48.790 --> 26:52.620
♪ Hold on ♪

26:52.620 --> 26:56.290
♪ Hold on to yourself ♪

26:56.290 --> 26:59.830
♪ For this is gonna
hurt like hell ♪

26:59.830 --> 27:01.500
-Scalpel.
-Scalpel.

27:01.500 --> 27:04.290
♪ Hell ♪

27:04.290 --> 27:06.710
♪♪

27:06.710 --> 27:08.790
[ Monitors beeping ]

27:08.790 --> 27:13.120
♪♪

27:13.120 --> 27:16.120
[ Whirring ]

27:16.120 --> 27:18.460
Is that when you and Richard
started talking?

27:18.460 --> 27:19.830
After the funeral?

27:19.830 --> 27:21.620
[ Breathing heavily ]

27:25.210 --> 27:27.670
I tried calling you.

27:27.670 --> 27:29.210
You never called back.

27:29.210 --> 27:30.420
And I worried.

27:30.420 --> 27:34.040
At first,
I was just checking in on you.

27:35.540 --> 27:39.170
Mm, Richard and I started...
[ Sniffs ]

27:39.170 --> 27:41.170
...talking about
a lot of things.

27:41.170 --> 27:44.540
We both
had amends to make.

27:44.540 --> 27:46.330
There are so many things

27:46.330 --> 27:50.040
I could say I'm sorry for,
Meredith.

27:50.040 --> 27:54.330
But all I really want to say
is thank you.

27:54.330 --> 27:56.710
Thank you for what?

27:56.710 --> 27:58.330
[ Exhales sharply ]

27:58.330 --> 28:03.420
For so long,
I measured my life

28:03.420 --> 28:08.750
in the things done to me,
taken from me.

28:08.750 --> 28:14.580
Now I can see my life
for exactly what it is.

28:14.580 --> 28:17.040
Some people have
more pain than others.

28:17.040 --> 28:20.380
But no one, nothing,
was conspiring against me.

28:20.380 --> 28:24.210
When you gave me
a piece of your liver,

28:24.210 --> 28:29.210
you gave me time,
precious time.

28:29.210 --> 28:32.580
Time to get your head
out of your own ass?

28:32.580 --> 28:35.540
[ Laughs ]

28:35.540 --> 28:40.210
[ Inhales deeply ]

28:40.210 --> 28:41.880
[ Coughs ]

28:41.880 --> 28:44.880
Y-- Y--
You could say that.

28:44.880 --> 28:51.290
I had a life, Meredith,
'cause of you.

28:51.290 --> 28:58.120
My own real, honest,
painful, incredible life.

28:58.120 --> 29:03.420
I just wish you
and I could have shared it.

29:03.420 --> 29:07.750
Well, I guess you did
try this time.

29:07.750 --> 29:09.420
I just didn't know.

29:09.420 --> 29:11.750
[ Laughs ]

29:11.750 --> 29:13.580
I miss Lexie.

29:13.580 --> 29:14.960
[ Laughs ]

29:14.960 --> 29:16.670
I miss her so much.

29:16.670 --> 29:20.460
Me too.

29:20.460 --> 29:23.920
I'm sorry you lost her.
[ Exhales sharply ]

29:23.920 --> 29:28.120
I know how much it -- it meant
to you, having a sister.

29:30.080 --> 29:32.250
I have another sister.

29:32.250 --> 29:36.620
But you and Molly,
you were never close.

29:36.620 --> 29:40.000
♪♪

29:40.000 --> 29:41.880
Her name is Maggie.

29:41.880 --> 29:44.500
Oh...

29:44.500 --> 29:47.000
She's brilliant.
And kind.

29:47.000 --> 29:51.210
She's the best of Ellis
and Richard.

29:51.210 --> 29:56.120
Your -- Your mother
and Richard had a baby.

29:56.120 --> 29:58.380
[ Breathes deeply ]

29:58.380 --> 30:02.000
♪♪

30:02.000 --> 30:05.460
At least something good
came from all that.

30:05.460 --> 30:07.460
♪♪

30:13.040 --> 30:16.580
[ Groans ] I'm gonna get
a humpback operating with you.

30:16.580 --> 30:17.830
Amelia: I'm already standing
on a step stool.

30:17.830 --> 30:18.540
what more do you want
from me?

30:18.540 --> 30:20.040
Heels?

30:20.040 --> 30:22.880
Okay,
it looks like the tumor

30:22.880 --> 30:24.080
is free of
the brachial plexus.

30:24.080 --> 30:25.250
Should we try
to pull it out?

30:25.250 --> 30:26.420
Let's do it.

30:26.420 --> 30:27.880
[ Beep ]

30:27.880 --> 30:29.080
EP Doc: We've lost
all the signal from one arm.

30:29.080 --> 30:31.380
The tumor
is moving pretty easily.

30:31.380 --> 30:32.710
Check your machine.
Could be artifact.

30:32.710 --> 30:35.330
No, there's still a little
tension from my side.

30:35.330 --> 30:37.920
I -- I think it's coming
from the root.

30:37.920 --> 30:40.250
Which means there's no way
to remove this without...

30:40.250 --> 30:41.670
Risking paralysis.

30:41.670 --> 30:43.540
♪♪

30:43.540 --> 30:44.830
[ Sighs ]

30:44.830 --> 30:45.920
If they can't remove
the whole tumor,

30:45.920 --> 30:47.500
they're gonna have to do it
piecemeal.

30:47.500 --> 30:49.080
Bailey:
But then they risk

30:49.080 --> 30:50.880
leaving some of the tumor
behind.

30:50.880 --> 30:55.670
♪♪

30:55.670 --> 30:57.460
What?

30:57.460 --> 31:02.380
♪♪

31:02.380 --> 31:03.710
My path pen.

31:03.710 --> 31:05.460
Remove the tumor piecemeal,

31:05.460 --> 31:07.460
and then use the pen
to see if you got it all.

31:07.460 --> 31:09.710
Okay, it hasn't cleared
FDA process yet,

31:09.710 --> 31:12.920
and it isn't on the market,
but I'm telling you, it works.

31:12.920 --> 31:16.710
♪♪

31:16.710 --> 31:19.080
Koracick: I really have
always liked you, Richard.

31:19.080 --> 31:21.290
No, you haven't.

31:21.290 --> 31:23.380
Amelia: Yes. Get it.

31:23.380 --> 31:28.380
♪♪

31:28.380 --> 31:29.920
[ Door closes ]

31:29.920 --> 31:31.210
Meredith: [ Laughs ]

31:31.210 --> 31:33.210
And that twitch
over her right eye

31:33.210 --> 31:34.750
when you switched
the ice maker

31:34.750 --> 31:35.960
from cubed to crushed.

31:35.960 --> 31:37.790
"What kind of a monster
crushes ice?

31:37.790 --> 31:39.080
It's uncivilized."

31:39.080 --> 31:41.790
Crushed ice
was uncivilized.

31:41.790 --> 31:43.420
Taking my last cup
of coffee...

31:43.420 --> 31:45.120
uncivilized.
Uncivilized.

31:45.120 --> 31:47.960
Getting an A-
in Chem Lab.

31:47.960 --> 31:49.750
Uncivilized.
Uncivilized.

31:49.750 --> 31:51.750
[ Laughs ] She was...

31:51.750 --> 31:52.920
Kind of a tyrant.

31:52.920 --> 31:54.080
But brilliant.

31:54.080 --> 31:56.420
Oh, I can't argue
with that.

31:56.420 --> 31:57.790
[ Laughs ]
Terrible driver.

31:57.790 --> 32:00.420
Can't argue with that.

32:00.420 --> 32:03.120
But she was
extraordinary.

32:03.120 --> 32:06.750
Yeah.
Oh.

32:06.750 --> 32:08.920
Do you regret
marrying her?

32:08.920 --> 32:10.920
[ Breathing heavily ]

32:10.920 --> 32:13.920
The entire time
she was pregnant with you,

32:13.920 --> 32:16.080
she pretended
she wasn't.

32:16.080 --> 32:19.620
I don't know if it was
stubbornness or denial.

32:19.620 --> 32:21.460
Maybe both.

32:21.460 --> 32:25.290
Nine months, she had to do
everything herself.

32:25.290 --> 32:27.710
And I had to let her.

32:27.710 --> 32:30.500
The night she went into labor,
she came home after surgery,

32:30.500 --> 32:35.670
and she just stood
in the doorway, wide-eyed.

32:35.670 --> 32:39.040
"We're having a baby,
Thatch.

32:39.040 --> 32:43.380
We're having a baby."
[ Laughs ]

32:43.380 --> 32:46.790
[ Breathes deeply ]

32:46.790 --> 32:50.000
As if the idea just hit her,
right there.

32:50.000 --> 32:53.000
She -- She started to laugh.
She couldn't stop laughing.

32:53.000 --> 32:56.620
Laughed all the way
to the hospital.

32:56.620 --> 32:59.620
I never heard her laugh
like that,

32:59.620 --> 33:03.500
so big, so free.

33:03.500 --> 33:05.750
♪♪

33:05.750 --> 33:09.330
And I just thought,
"Wow.

33:09.330 --> 33:13.500
What a way for you
to come into the world."

33:13.500 --> 33:17.250
We weren't perfect.

33:17.250 --> 33:20.420
We weren't even happy
a lot of the time.

33:20.420 --> 33:24.000
But I'd marry her
all over again

33:24.000 --> 33:28.330
for that night,
that laugh.

33:28.330 --> 33:30.210
And you.

33:30.210 --> 33:33.330
And this.

33:33.330 --> 33:38.500
I'd do it all again
for this.

33:38.500 --> 33:45.080
♪♪

33:45.080 --> 33:46.920
[ Buzzer ]

33:46.920 --> 33:48.120
Koracick: How can there
still be cancer there?

33:48.120 --> 33:49.380
We've been at this
for hours.

33:49.380 --> 33:50.880
It's still lighting up
like Christmas.

33:50.880 --> 33:53.290
Let's just keep going.

33:53.290 --> 33:55.710
We'll hit clear tissue
eventually.

33:55.710 --> 33:57.880
[ Buzzer ]

33:57.880 --> 33:59.040
[ Beep ]
EP Doc: Signal's fading again.

33:59.040 --> 34:00.540
She's losing function
in her arms.

34:00.540 --> 34:02.710
We've barely touched anything.
Amelia: Breathe.

34:02.710 --> 34:05.540
We are going
in the right direction.

34:05.540 --> 34:06.710
Losing the signal
in her other arm --

34:06.710 --> 34:08.880
Okay, stop it! We know!
If we keep going,

34:08.880 --> 34:10.460
we cost Catherine
her motor function,

34:10.460 --> 34:12.540
her career, her life
as she knows it -- we know!

34:12.540 --> 34:17.750
♪♪

34:17.750 --> 34:23.210
♪♪

34:23.210 --> 34:25.000
Meredith...

34:25.000 --> 34:26.960
Okay,
don't try to speak.

34:26.960 --> 34:29.790
But...the closet.

34:29.790 --> 34:31.000
I left something...

34:31.000 --> 34:34.290
I don't need anything.

34:34.290 --> 34:36.750
...for your kids.

34:36.750 --> 34:38.750
[ Breathing heavily ]

34:38.750 --> 34:41.080
I wish...

34:41.080 --> 34:43.830
I wish I knew them.

34:43.830 --> 34:47.580
I thought of --
I thought of them.

34:47.580 --> 34:50.750
[ Exhales sharply ]

34:50.750 --> 34:52.620
Ahh.

34:52.620 --> 34:56.750
Your hands are so cold.

34:56.750 --> 34:57.670
Sorry, I can --

34:57.670 --> 35:01.170
No, no, no.

35:01.170 --> 35:02.830
Oh, it feels good.

35:02.830 --> 35:09.120
♪♪

35:09.120 --> 35:14.290
Zola is so smart
and so strong.

35:14.290 --> 35:17.380
Yeah?
And she keeps me on my toes

35:17.380 --> 35:19.880
every minute
of every day.

35:19.880 --> 35:24.120
And Bailey says "funny"
before every sentence.

35:24.120 --> 35:26.710
"Funny,
I'd like an apple.

35:26.710 --> 35:28.880
Funny, I need pajamas."

35:28.880 --> 35:32.120
It's so cute.

35:32.120 --> 35:36.460
And Ellis...
she is brave.

35:36.460 --> 35:39.960
And she's obsessed
with hip-hop.

35:39.960 --> 35:45.830
They are exhausting...
and amazing.

35:45.830 --> 35:48.330
♪♪

35:48.330 --> 35:52.170
I wish you knew them,
too.

35:52.170 --> 35:55.580
Because they are so,
so beautiful.

35:55.580 --> 36:00.170
[ Exhales deeply ]

36:00.170 --> 36:06.830
♪♪

36:06.830 --> 36:10.500
[ Exhales heavily ]

36:10.500 --> 36:17.000
♪♪

36:17.000 --> 36:23.710
♪♪

36:23.710 --> 36:25.250
[ Sighs heavily ]

36:33.540 --> 36:35.380
[ Monitors beeping ]

36:41.040 --> 36:42.040
How...

36:43.710 --> 36:45.710
Easy. Easy, Mom.

36:45.710 --> 36:48.540
Catherine: How -- How --
Easy, easy, easy, easy.

36:48.540 --> 36:49.880
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh, shh.

36:49.880 --> 36:52.040
Hey.

36:52.040 --> 36:54.080
-Mm-hmm.
-Uh-huh.
-I feel that.

36:54.080 --> 36:57.380
Okay.
Hold on, hold on.

36:57.380 --> 37:01.120
All right. Well,
your reflexes are normal.

37:01.120 --> 37:05.250
My hands and feet move.
Whoo.

37:05.250 --> 37:08.580
I'm not dead?
With that tumor?

37:08.580 --> 37:10.540
No, you're most definitely
not dead.

37:10.540 --> 37:12.500
Oh, I thought for sure
they were gonna kill me.

37:16.620 --> 37:21.250
What?

37:21.250 --> 37:23.080
Tell me.

37:23.080 --> 37:26.290
Catherine, when we went in
to get the tumor,

37:26.290 --> 37:28.960
it was adherent
to your brachial plexus.

37:28.960 --> 37:32.250
Koracick: We were able
to remove about 95% of it,

37:32.250 --> 37:35.580
but we had to leave
one nodule behind.

37:35.580 --> 37:40.420
So...radiation? Chemo?

37:42.750 --> 37:45.460
They've had some success
with proton beam therapy.

37:45.460 --> 37:47.420
Some?

37:47.420 --> 37:51.960
It's likely,
even with treatment...

37:51.960 --> 37:54.000
I'll have to live
with this cancer

37:54.000 --> 37:56.120
the rest of my life.

37:56.120 --> 38:00.670
I was sure you'd get it all
or kill me trying.

38:00.670 --> 38:02.670
So did we.

38:02.670 --> 38:05.120
Catherine,
I'm so sorry.

38:06.500 --> 38:09.330
Sorry? I'm alive.

38:09.330 --> 38:13.120
I can live with this
for many years.

38:13.120 --> 38:17.290
People live with cancer.
We've all seen it happen.

38:17.290 --> 38:18.830
You're gonna have to get, uh,
scans every three months

38:18.830 --> 38:21.120
to make sure the tumor
doesn't, uh, grow.

38:21.120 --> 38:22.790
And in between,
I'll operate.

38:22.790 --> 38:25.210
Mm.
And I'll hug my son.

38:25.210 --> 38:27.000
Mm.

38:27.000 --> 38:29.460
Make love to my husband.

38:29.460 --> 38:30.670
Okay...

38:30.670 --> 38:34.620
Chase my Harriet,
make mistakes,

38:34.620 --> 38:37.330
and fight about who gets
to pick the movie on date night.

38:37.330 --> 38:39.000
[ Chuckles ]

38:41.670 --> 38:44.040
You two have given me
my life back.

38:44.040 --> 38:46.000
[ Chuckles ]

38:46.000 --> 38:47.670
Now what?

38:47.670 --> 38:48.920
'Cause we didn't
plan on this.

38:48.920 --> 38:50.750
[ Laughs ]

38:50.750 --> 38:53.040
These two pulled off
a miracle.

38:53.040 --> 38:56.710
Miracles aren't always
punctuation marks.

38:56.710 --> 38:58.710
But they are worth celebrating.

38:58.710 --> 39:01.170
So we are gonna have
that party.

39:01.170 --> 39:04.210
We just might have to wait
a couple of months

39:04.210 --> 39:05.920
so I can get
on the dance floor.

39:05.920 --> 39:07.580
[ Laughs ]
[ Chuckles ]

39:07.580 --> 39:10.500
I love you.

39:10.500 --> 39:11.670
♪♪

39:11.670 --> 39:13.830
[ Both laugh ]

39:13.830 --> 39:15.040
[ Smooches ]

39:15.040 --> 39:16.000
[ Elevator bell dings ]

39:21.710 --> 39:24.460
[ Telephone rings ]

39:24.460 --> 39:28.290
[ Indistinct talking over P.A. ]

39:28.290 --> 39:30.620
Teddy: Hey.
I heard about the surgery.

39:30.620 --> 39:31.790
Congratulations.

39:31.790 --> 39:33.080
Oh. I know, I know.

39:33.080 --> 39:34.290
You knew I had it in me
all along.

39:34.290 --> 39:35.880
Honestly?
I was on the fence.

39:37.960 --> 39:39.880
[ Laughs ]

39:39.880 --> 39:42.460
You should be
really proud.

39:42.460 --> 39:44.960
There are not a lot of surgeons
who could do that.

39:44.960 --> 39:46.580
Which part?

39:46.580 --> 39:48.040
Where I flipped my friend
like a pancake

39:48.040 --> 39:49.960
or failed to leave her
cancer free?

39:49.960 --> 39:51.920
The part where
you saved her life

39:51.920 --> 39:53.540
and her surgical career.

39:56.250 --> 39:58.290
Yeah, that part
wasn't half bad.

40:00.750 --> 40:03.080
You should celebrate.

40:03.080 --> 40:04.750
Why don't you get
cleaned up?

40:04.750 --> 40:06.120
I'll meet you at Joe's,
and I'll buy you a drink.

40:06.120 --> 40:08.290
Uh...w--
Can we take a rain check?

40:08.290 --> 40:10.830
I...I'm wiped.
And I-I smell bad.

40:10.830 --> 40:15.420
And when you spend money on me,
I want to smell good.

40:15.420 --> 40:17.420
[ Elevator bell dings ]
Yeah. Okay.

40:17.420 --> 40:18.580
Night.

40:18.580 --> 40:20.580
Goodnight.

40:20.580 --> 40:25.750
♪ Red lights are flashing
on the highway ♪

40:25.750 --> 40:27.750
Meredith:
When it comes to medicine,

40:27.750 --> 40:31.120
who's to say
what is winning or losing?

40:31.120 --> 40:34.120
♪ I wonder if we're gonna ever
get home tonight ♪

40:34.120 --> 40:35.750
There's just as much value
in trying again

40:35.750 --> 40:39.120
as there is in letting go...

40:39.120 --> 40:43.000
♪ But if you break down ♪
Koracick: I saved my friend
today, David.

40:43.000 --> 40:45.460
♪ I'll drive out and find you ♪

40:45.460 --> 40:48.620
I didn't think I-I could,
and it wasn't perfect.

40:48.620 --> 40:51.170
♪ If you forget my love ♪
[ Laughs ]

40:51.170 --> 40:53.620
Your dad was kind of a badass.

40:53.620 --> 40:55.830
♪ I'll try to remind you ♪

40:55.830 --> 40:59.380
...letting go of suffering,
regret, pain, fear.

40:59.380 --> 41:03.290
♪ And stay by you ♪

41:03.290 --> 41:08.120
♪ When it don't come easy ♪

41:08.120 --> 41:11.790
♪ When it don't come easy ♪

41:11.790 --> 41:19.620
♪♪

41:19.620 --> 41:20.540
♪ I don't know nothing
except change will come ♪

41:20.540 --> 41:27.210
I operated on a freaking
legend's spine today.

41:27.210 --> 41:29.420
And it was terrifying.
[ Chuckles ]

41:29.420 --> 41:32.210
And exhilarating.

41:32.210 --> 41:34.830
And imperfect.

41:34.830 --> 41:37.210
♪ I wonder if we're gonna
ever get home ♪

41:37.210 --> 41:40.670
Mostly terrifying.
[ Chuckles ]

41:40.670 --> 41:42.250
Because she's not
just a legend.

41:42.250 --> 41:45.420
She matters so much
to so many people that I love...

41:45.420 --> 41:47.500
♪ And all of the signs
got blown away ♪

41:47.500 --> 41:50.040
♪ Sometimes you wonder if you're
walking in the wrong direction ♪

41:50.040 --> 41:51.830
Most of my life,
I have been chasing

41:51.830 --> 41:56.670
the kind of high
that I feel right now.

41:56.670 --> 41:59.380
♪ But if you break down ♪
[ Sniffles ]

41:59.380 --> 42:02.670
I gave a surgeon back
her hands today.

42:02.670 --> 42:07.460
I gave a husband his wife,
a son his mother.

42:07.460 --> 42:11.120
[ Sighs ]

42:11.120 --> 42:13.880
And I am so incredibly grateful
to be sober...

42:13.880 --> 42:16.120
[ Exhales sharply ]

42:16.120 --> 42:18.120
...to be present enough
to have felt

42:18.120 --> 42:23.710
every terrifying,
exhilarating,

42:23.710 --> 42:26.120
imperfect moment.

42:26.120 --> 42:28.710
♪ When it don't come easy ♪

42:28.710 --> 42:30.540
Instead of saying
someone we love

42:30.540 --> 42:36.120
is battling, beating, fighting,
winning, or losing,

42:36.120 --> 42:37.540
why don't we just
tell the truth.

42:37.540 --> 42:39.210
♪ So many things
that I had before ♪

42:39.210 --> 42:41.460
Meredith:
There you go, sweethearts.

42:41.460 --> 42:43.460
♪ That don't matter
to me now ♪

42:43.460 --> 42:45.500
We get sick.
We take our medicine...

42:45.500 --> 42:47.290
♪♪

42:47.290 --> 42:49.920
Zola: Wow. So cool.

42:49.920 --> 42:51.920
Where did you get it,
Mommy?

42:51.920 --> 42:54.500
Uh, your grandfather,
Thatcher.

42:54.500 --> 42:57.330
He wanted you to have it,
and he wanted you to know

42:57.330 --> 42:58.920
that he cared about you
very much...

42:58.920 --> 43:00.580
Funny, I love it.

43:00.580 --> 43:03.790
...some of us live, some die.

43:03.790 --> 43:06.750
Mommy, are you okay?

43:06.750 --> 43:12.750
♪ When it don't come easy ♪
Yes, Zo-Zo. I will be fine.

43:12.750 --> 43:16.330
♪ When it don't come easy ♪

43:16.330 --> 43:18.460
♪♪

43:26.580 --> 43:34.790
♪♪

43:34.790 --> 43:43.290
♪♪

43:43.290 --> 43:51.500
♪♪
